INSERT INTO `helpcenter_topic` VALUES ('32039', 'How to create a data quality rule?', '<h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; position: static;\"><span style=\'font-size: 16pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\'>Creating a data quality rule</span></h3><p><br style=\"position: static;\"></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; position: static;\"><span style=\'font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\'>To create a data quality rule in the data quality rule summary page,</span></p><ol style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-inline-start: 48px; position: static;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\'list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 10pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: -18pt; position: static;\'><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; position: static;\"><span style=\'font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\'>Go to the Governance Catalog &gt;&nbsp;</span><span style=\'font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\'>Data Quality Rule</span><span style=\'font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\'>.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\'list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 10pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: -18pt; position: static;\'><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; position: static;\"><span style=\'font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\'>Click <strong>Add Rule</strong>&nbsp;</span><span style=\'font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\'>to create a new data quality rule.</span></p></li></ol><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-left: 18pt; text-indent: -36pt; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding: 0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; position: static;\"><span style=\'font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\'>The data quality rule page opens to define all the parameters.</span></p><ol start=\"3\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-inline-start: 48px; position: static;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\'list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 10pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: -18pt; position: static;\'><span style=\'font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\'>In the Add Rule page, enter the following:</span></li></ol><ul style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-inline-start: 48px; position: static;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\'list-style-type: disc; font-size: 10pt; font-family: \"Noto Sans Symbols\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; position: static;\'><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; position: static;\"><span style=\'font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\'>Domain&nbsp;</span><span style=\'font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\'>- Select the Domain name from the list that has the business term.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\'list-style-type: disc; font-size: 10pt; font-family: \"Noto Sans Symbols\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; position: static;\'><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; position: static;\"><span style=\'font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\'>Rule Name</span><span style=\'font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\'>&nbsp;- Name that identifies the rule to be written.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\'list-style-type: disc; font-size: 10pt; font-family: \"Noto Sans Symbols\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; position: static;\'><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; position: static;\"><span style=\'font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\'>Business Term</span><span style=\'font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\'>&nbsp;- The term that governs the data quality rule.&nbsp;</span></p></li><li><p><span style=\'font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\'>Purpose</span><span style=\'font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\'>&nbsp;- Description defining the need for this data quality rule.</span></p></li></ul>', 'gdq.addrule', '1', '', '', 'admin', '2022-05-30 13:48:21', '2022-05-30 13:48:21', null);
INSERT INTO `helpcenter_topic` VALUES ('32040', 'How to add a GDQ?', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt; position: static;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\">To create a Governed data Query in the&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\">Governed Data Query Summary Page,</span></span></span></p><ol style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-inline-start: 48px; position: static;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\'list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: -18pt; position: static;\'><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; position: static;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\">Go to Governance Catalog &gt; Governed Data Query.</span></span></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\'list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: -18pt; position: static;\'><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; position: static;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\">Click the <strong>Add GDQ</strong> icon&nbsp;to create a new GDQ.</span></span></span></p></li></ol><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-left: 27pt; text-indent: -36pt; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding: 0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; position: static;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\">The add GDQ page opens to create a Governed Data Query.</span></span></span></p><ol start=\"3\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-inline-start: 48px; position: static;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\'list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: -18pt; position: static;\'><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; position: static;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\">On the Add GDQ page, enter the following</span></span></span></p></li></ol><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-indent: 36pt; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; position: static;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\">GDQ name</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\">-A unique name for the Governed data Query</span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-left: 36pt; text-indent: -36pt; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding: 0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; position: static;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\">Domain</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\">- Select the Domain name from the list that has the privacy terms</span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-left: 36pt; text-indent: -36pt; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding: 0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; position: static;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\">Steward</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\">-</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\">Approver for the Governed Data Query</span></span></span></p><ol start=\"4\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding-inline-start: 48px; position: static;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\'list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"Helvetica Neue\", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; margin-left: -18pt; position: static;\'><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; position: static;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\">Click&nbsp;</span><strong>Add GDQ&nbsp;</strong>button&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\">to create and display the data query on the summary page.</span></p></li></ol>', 'gdq.addgdq', '1', '', '', 'admin', '2022-05-30 13:48:21', '2022-05-30 13:48:21', null);
INSERT INTO `helpcenter_topic` VALUES ('32041', 'How to create a new certified policy?', '<p><span data-sheets-userformat=\'{\"2\":15165,\"3\":{\"1\":0},\"5\":{\"1\":[{\"1\":2,\"2\":0,\"5\":[null,2,0]},{\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":3},{\"1\":1,\"2\":0,\"4\":1}]},\"6\":{\"1\":[{\"1\":2,\"2\":0,\"5\":[null,2,0]},{\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":3},{\"1\":1,\"2\":0,\"4\":1}]},\"7\":{\"1\":[{\"1\":2,\"2\":0,\"5\":[null,2,0]},{\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":3},{\"1\":1,\"2\":0,\"4\":1}]},\"8\":{\"1\":[{\"1\":2,\"2\":0,\"5\":[null,2,0]},{\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":3},{\"1\":1,\"2\":0,\"4\":1}]},\"11\":4,\"12\":0,\"14\":[null,2,16711680],\"15\":\"Arial\",\"16\":10}\' data-sheets-value=\'{\"1\":2,\"2\":\"A user can add policy by the select the domain, provide a name to the policy, and select the policy type as &#8216;Certify&#8217;.\"}\' style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); position: static;\">A user can add policy by the selecting the domain, provide a name to the policy, and select the policy type as &lsquo;Certify&rsquo;.</span> </p>', 'cert.addpolicy', '1', '', '', 'admin', '2022-05-30 13:48:21', '2022-05-30 13:48:21', null);
INSERT INTO `helpcenter_topic` VALUES ('32042', 'How to raise a new service request in service desk module?', '<p><span style=\"font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">To raise a new service request<br style=\"position: static;\">Navigate to the Governance catalog &gt; &nbsp;Servicedesk module.</span></p><ul><li><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\">Click on <strong>New Service Request</strong> button, a popup of new connection displayed.&nbsp;</span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\">From the drop-down list search or select the required ticket template.<br style=\"position: static;\">Click on the Continue button, the selected ticket template page is displayed.&nbsp;</span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\">Enter all the details as requested in template according to the type of request raised.&nbsp;</span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\">Click on the <strong>Submit</strong> button. It will generate a new new service desk ticket (Request ID)</span></span></span></li></ul><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;\">Note: In the summary page of the service desk request , there is an external application JIRA ticket number link that will get mapped and navigate to the JIRA application. Click on JIRA ticket Id then page will be redirected to external ticket number summary page. If ticket creation fails in an external system, &nbsp;then the &ldquo;repost&rdquo; option will retry to push the ticket to JIRA.&nbsp;</span></span></p><p><br></p>', 'new.servicerequest', '1', '', '', 'admin', '2022-05-30 13:48:21', '2022-05-30 13:48:21', null);
INSERT INTO `helpcenter_topic` VALUES ('32043', 'How to add a new connection with an external application?', '<div style=\"position: static;\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><strong>Navigate to Administration &gt; Manage Service Desk &gt; Service Desk Integration. </strong></span></div><ul><li><div style=\"position: static;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\">Click on <strong>Service Desk Integration&nbsp;</strong>button, it shows the JIRA/ServiceNow tab.&nbsp;<br></span></span></span></div></li><li><div style=\"position: static;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\">Click on ServiceNow button.</span></span></span></div></li><li><div style=\"position: static;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; float: none; position: static; display: inline !important;\">To establish connection enter the following parameters,</span></span></span></span></div></li><li style=\"margin-left: 20px;\"><div style=\"position: static;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\">Enter the Connection Name: <em>Name of a ServiceNow connection(User-defined).</em></span></span></span></div></li><li style=\"margin-left: 20px;\"><div style=\"position: static;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\">ServiceNow Server: <em>&nbsp;Instance URL.</em></span></span></span></div></li><li style=\"margin-left: 20px;\"><div style=\"position: static;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\">Username: <em>Authorised email id associated with ServiceNow account password.</em></span></span></span></div></li><li style=\"margin-left: 20px;\"><div style=\"position: static;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\">ServiceNow Token: <em>ServiceNow account password.</em></span></span></span></div></li><li><div style=\"position: static;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\">Click on Validate, and then new connection is established.</span></span></span></div></li></ul><div style=\"position: static;\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Similarly, you can follow same steps to perform JIRA integration</span></div><p><br style=\"position: static;\"><br></p>', 'add.newconnection', '1', '', '', 'admin', '2022-05-30 13:48:21', '2022-05-30 13:48:21', null);
INSERT INTO `helpcenter_topic` VALUES ('32044', 'What is Mapper column?', '<p><span data-sheets-userformat=\'{\"2\":14909,\"3\":{\"1\":0},\"5\":{\"1\":[{\"1\":2,\"2\":0,\"5\":{\"1\":2,\"2\":0}},{\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":3},{\"1\":1,\"2\":0,\"4\":1}]},\"6\":{\"1\":[{\"1\":2,\"2\":0,\"5\":{\"1\":2,\"2\":0}},{\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":3},{\"1\":1,\"2\":0,\"4\":1}]},\"7\":{\"1\":[{\"1\":2,\"2\":0,\"5\":{\"1\":2,\"2\":0}},{\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":3},{\"1\":1,\"2\":0,\"4\":1}]},\"8\":{\"1\":[{\"1\":2,\"2\":0,\"5\":{\"1\":2,\"2\":0}},{\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":3},{\"1\":1,\"2\":0,\"4\":1}]},\"12\":0,\"14\":{\"1\":2,\"2\":16711680},\"15\":\"Arial\",\"16\":11}\' data-sheets-value=\'{\"1\":2,\"2\":\"Mapper column displays the icon of external tools (JIRA or ServiceNow). With this, it maps the tickets from the OvalEdge application to the JIRA or Service now tool.  The tickets which are mapped to external tools are displayed in the Service Desk page.\"}\' style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); position: static;\">Mapper column displays the icon of external tools (JIRA or ServiceNow). With this, it maps the tickets from the OvalEdge application to the JIRA or Service now tool. &nbsp;The tickets which are mapped to external tools are displayed in the Service Desk page.</span></p>', 'map.columns', '1', '', '', 'admin', '2022-05-30 13:48:21', '2022-05-30 13:48:21', null);
INSERT INTO `helpcenter_topic` VALUES ('32045', 'How to add policy rule?', '<div style=\"position: static;\"><strong><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">To Add Policy Rule, </span></strong></div><ul><li><span style=\"font-size: 14px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;\">Navigate to Governance Catalog - &gt; Certification Policy</span></li><li><div style=\"position: static;\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Select Policy name.</span></span></span></div></li><li><div style=\"position: static;\"><span style=\"font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Click on + plus icon to Add Policy rule.</span></span></span></div></li></ul><div style=\"position: static;\"><br></div><p><span data-sheets-userformat=\'{\"2\":14909,\"3\":{\"1\":0},\"5\":{\"1\":[{\"1\":2,\"2\":0,\"5\":{\"1\":2,\"2\":0}},{\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":3},{\"1\":1,\"2\":0,\"4\":1}]},\"6\":{\"1\":[{\"1\":2,\"2\":0,\"5\":{\"1\":2,\"2\":0}},{\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":3},{\"1\":1,\"2\":0,\"4\":1}]},\"7\":{\"1\":[{\"1\":2,\"2\":0,\"5\":{\"1\":2,\"2\":0}},{\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":3},{\"1\":1,\"2\":0,\"4\":1}]},\"8\":{\"1\":[{\"1\":2,\"2\":0,\"5\":{\"1\":2,\"2\":0}},{\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":3},{\"1\":1,\"2\":0,\"4\":1}]},\"12\":0,\"14\":{\"1\":2,\"2\":16711680},\"15\":\"Arial\",\"16\":11}\' data-sheets-value=\'{\"1\":2,\"2\":\"The available rules are as follows:\r\na. Glossary Term Present: On the selected trigger object, for example, if it is a\r\ntable, the percentage of columns that has business glossary terms are\r\nvalidated using this rule.\r\nNote: It is mandatory that the user associates a TERM to Table/ Report/ File\r\nfor the policy rule to act on. Based on the threshold set for the policy the Table/\r\nReport/ File gets certified.\r\nb. Business Description Present: On the selected trigger object, for example,\r\nif it is a table, the percentage of columns that has business definitions and\r\ntechnical definitions present is validated using this rule.\r\nNote: It is mandatory that the user adds business description to Table/ Report/\r\nFile for the policy rule to act on. Based on the threshold set for the policy the\r\nTable/ Report/ File gets certified.\r\nc. Lineage Present: On the selected trigger object, for example, if it is a table,\r\nthe number of upstream objects that the trigger object has is validated\"}\' style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); position: static;\"><strong>The available rules are as follows:</strong></span></p><ul><li><span data-sheets-userformat=\'{\"2\":14909,\"3\":{\"1\":0},\"5\":{\"1\":[{\"1\":2,\"2\":0,\"5\":{\"1\":2,\"2\":0}},{\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":3},{\"1\":1,\"2\":0,\"4\":1}]},\"6\":{\"1\":[{\"1\":2,\"2\":0,\"5\":{\"1\":2,\"2\":0}},{\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":3},{\"1\":1,\"2\":0,\"4\":1}]},\"7\":{\"1\":[{\"1\":2,\"2\":0,\"5\":{\"1\":2,\"2\":0}},{\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":3},{\"1\":1,\"2\":0,\"4\":1}]},\"8\":{\"1\":[{\"1\":2,\"2\":0,\"5\":{\"1\":2,\"2\":0}},{\"1\":0,\"2\":0,\"3\":3},{\"1\":1,\"2\":0,\"4\":1}]},\"12\":0,\"14\":{\"1\":2,\"2\":16711680},\"15\":\"Arial\",\"16\":11}\' data-sheets-value=\'{\"1\":2,\"2\":\"The available rules are as follows:\r\na. Glossary Term Present: On the selected trigger object, for example, if it is a\r\ntable, the percentage of columns that has business glossary terms are\r\nvalidated using this rule.\r\nNote: It is mandatory that the user associates a TERM to Table/ Report/ File\r\nfor the policy rule to act on. Based on the threshold set for the policy the Table/\r\nReport/ File gets certified.\r\nb. Business Description Present: On the selected trigger object, for example,\r\nif it is a table, the percentage of columns that has business definitions and\r\ntechnical definitions present is validated using this rule.\r\nNote: It is mandatory that the user adds business descri